# =====================================================================
# Root .gitignore  (per-project .gitignore files add data/ allow-listing)
# =====================================================================

# --- Build artifacts: every generated subdir under any build/, plus x64/ ---
**/build/*/
**/x64/
.vs/
*.obj
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.exp
*.lib
*.idb
*.tlog
*.log
*.exe

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# --- Secrets / credentials (never commit) ---
.env
*.env
*.key
*.pem
secrets.*
*token*

# --- OS / editor noise ---
Thumbs.db
.DS_Store

# --- Pre-existing catalog-generation pipeline (kept LOCAL, not published) ---
# The source-of-truth inputs (CUDA_CPP_Healthcare_Projects.xlsx +
# CUDA_CPP_Healthcare_Projects_DeepDive.md) and the generated catalog.json ARE
# committed. The upstream scratch artifacts that produced them are not
# (CLAUDE.md §2-§3): they would just confuse a learner cloning the repo.
projects.json
raw_part_*.md
assemble.py
build_xlsx.py
CUDA_CPP_Healthcare_Projects.md
START_PROMPT.md
.~lock.*#
